snippet.textDisplay: If the numbers are correct, this car will get to 180 mph as fast as my car will get to 60 mph.  If my math is correct this car is 3 times faster, has 14 times as much power, but costs 666 times as much.    If this car was 666 times faster than my car it would reach 39, 960 mph (52 times the speed of sound) in >9 seconds, and if it had 666 times as much power it would produce 93,240 horsepower.  That would make the power to weight ratio  more than 10 times that of the Saturn V rocket that brought us to the moon.  Under full acceleration this hypothetical car would produce 480 g forces making my felt weight 36 tons, or about 1/3 the weight of a blue whale.  Good thing this car isn't linear in cost to power compared to my old sedan.... :)
